    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - HUBS, BEARINGS, AND SEALS - REAR DRIVE AXLES</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="describe" graphiccount="2">
        <title>REAR DRIVE AXLES</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Prelubricate inner and outer bearings with a coating of recommended oil bearing lube.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Assemble bearings and seal as described in section
                <hotlnk document="s14001t_10.xml" xrefid="hl1400106">WHEEL SEALS
                    <xref refid="hl1400106"/>
                </hotlnk>
                .
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use a wheel dolly to place the wheel/hub assembly on the axle tube spindle. Care must be
                taken so that the seal is not damaged when sliding hub assembly onto spindle (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1400128">Figure 30</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1400128" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1400128" filename="../figg14/G1400128.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="272px" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 30. Head-on View of Installing Wheel (Hub) Assembly Using a Wheel Dolly</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. RIM</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. WHEEL (HUB)</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. INNER BEARING</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. AXLE/SPINDLE</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Fill wheel or hub cavity with differential lubricant to level of largest bearing cup.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Adjust wheel bearings. Refer to
                <hotlnk document="s14001t_7.xml" xrefid="hl1400104">WHEEL BEARING ADJUSTMENT
                    <xref refid="hl1400104"/>
                </hotlnk>
                .
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install axle shaft (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1400129">Figure 31</hotlnk>). Refer to GROUP 14 - REAR AXLES in the CTS-5000 Master
                Service Manual for axle shaft specifications.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1400129" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1400129" filename="../figg14/G1400129.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="232px" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 31. Rear Axle Shaft Installation</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Check differential for proper lubricant level.</para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
